-- Pawnbroker Albemarle & Bond to appoint administrators
-- By Paul Sandle
-- Tue Mar 25, 2014 05:19AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, March 25 (Reuters) - British pawnbroker Albemarle & Bond <ALBH.L> said it would appoint administrators on Tuesday after its lenders declined to  support any rescue plans for the loss-making business.

The company, which said on Monday its shareholders would see no return on their investment, said that without the support of its banks it would shortly be unable to meets it liabilities. [ID:nASM000636] "In such circumstances, the appointment of an administrator is the most appropriate course of action," it said. It said it would file notice of intention to appoint four insolvency practitioners from PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as joint administrators to Albemarle as soon as is practically possible.